GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 598
Short Title: Change to Low-Performing Schools Designation. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Sawyer (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODIFY THE CRITERIA FOR EVALUATING LOW-PERFORMING
3 SCHOOLS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 115C-105.37(a) reads as rewritten:
6 "(a) Identification of Low-Performing Schools. – The State Board of Education shall
7 identify low-performing schools on an annual basis. Low-performing schools are those that earn
8 an overall school performance grade of D or F and a school growth score of "met expected
9 growth" or "not met expected growth" as defined by G.S. 115C-83.15."
10 SECTION 2. G.S. 115C-105.37(b) reads as rewritten:
11 "(b) Parental Notice of Low-Performing School Status. – Each school that the State Board
12 identifies as low-performing shall provide written notification to the parents and guardians of
13 students attending that school within 30 days of the identification that includes the following
14 information:
15 (1) A statement that the State Board of Education has found that the school has
16 earned an overall school performance grade of D or F and a school growth
17 score of "met expected growth" or "not met expected growth" and has been
18 identified as a low-performing school as defined by G.S. 115C-105.37. The
19 statement shall include an explanation of the school performance grades and
20 growth scores.
21 …."
22 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to identification
23 of low performing schools based on data from the 2025-2026 school year.
*S598-v-1*

